The paper deals with natural language understanding for mobile service robots, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding. "cs.RO" (Robotics) is also highly likely, as the paper focuses on implementing the system in a robot. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category, as the paper uses deep learning techniques for natural language understanding. "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is also a possible category, as the paper uses recurrent neural networks and long short-term memory networks for action detection and slot filling. Finally, "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper compares different word embedding algorithms for input to the neural networks.
